-- Ivory Coast Inflation Rate Increases to 3.6% in February
-- B y   B a u d e l a i r e   M i e u
-- 2013-03-18T13:13:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-18/ivory-coast-inflation-rate-increases-to-3-6-in-february.html
Inflation in  Ivory Coast , the
worldâ€™s biggest cocoa producer, accelerated to 3.6 percent in
February as costs of food and education climbed.  The rate rose from 3.4 percent in January, the Abidjan-
based  National Institute of Statistics  said in two separate e-
mailed statements today. Prices increased 0.1 percent in the
month.  Food and soft-drinks costs rose 4.1 percent in February
from a year earlier, while housing and utilities were 3.6
percent higher. The cost of education soared 28.7 percent, the
institute said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
